# Project Configuration

## Technology Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| UI | React 19 |
| State | Zustand 5 (global) + TanStack Query 5 (server) |
| Language | TypeScript 6.0 strict |
| Bundler | Vite 8 (Rolldown + Oxc — official `vite` package) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS **v4** (CSS-based config — no tailwind.config.ts) |
| Components | shadcn/ui (new-york style) |
| Routing | React Router v7 |
| Forms | react-hook-form v7 + zod v4 |
| i18n | i18next 26 + react-i18next 17 |
| Testing | Vitest 4 + Testing Library |

## Tailwind v4 (CRITICAL)

**There is no `tailwind.config.ts`.** All config in `src/index.css`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "tw-animate-css";
@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));

@theme inline {
  --color-primary: hsl(var(--primary));
  /* ... all tokens here */
}

:root { --primary: 221.2 83.2% 53.3%; }
.dark { --primary: 217.2 91.2% 59.8%; }
```

- Dark mode via `.dark` class (NOT `darkMode: 'class'` in JS config — that file doesn't exist).
- Animations via `tw-animate-css` package (CSS import, not a PostCSS plugin).
- `@tailwindcss/vite` handles compilation — do NOT add tailwindcss to PostCSS.
- Adding new color token: add HSL value to `:root`, map in `@theme inline`.

## i18n

- Translations in `public/locales/{lng}/{ns}.json`
- Namespaces: `common` (always loaded), `errors` (always loaded), page-specific (lazy), feature-specific (lazy on demand)
- Language detection: `localStorage` → browser → fallback `'en'`
- HMR: auto-reload translations in dev when files in `public/locales/` change
- No hardcoded user-visible strings — always use `t('key')`.

```typescript
const { t } = useTranslation(['common', 'home']);
return <h1>{t('home:title')}</h1>;
```

## UI Quality — avoid the "AI aesthetic"

AI-generated UI has recognizable tells. For any UI work reject the framework default in favour of this repo's tokens (`src/index.css` → `@theme inline {}` + `:root`/`.dark`):

- **Brand colour**: the palette is **Google Blue** (`--primary: 221.2 83.2% 53.3%`, dark `217.2 91.2% 59.8%`) — never the default purple/indigo. Use `bg-primary`/`text-primary`, never hard-coded hex.
- **Radius scale**: respect the hierarchy — `--radius-sm` / `--radius-md` / `--radius-lg`, all derived from `--radius: 0.5rem`. Don't round everything to the max; vary radius by element weight.
- **Gradients**: none ship by default. Flat fills only; add a gradient only when a real design sanctions it.
- **Spacing & shadows**: use Tailwind's spacing scale and shadcn's subtle elevation — no uniform oversized padding, no shadow-heavy depth.
- **Charts**: use the five `--chart-1`…`--chart-5` tokens, not ad-hoc colours.
- **Layout**: content-first and priority-driven, not a generic hero + uniform card grid. LCP-critical content first.
- **Copy**: realistic strings via `t()` (see i18n above), never lorem-ipsum — placeholder copy hides real wrapping / overflow / length.
- **Components**: shadcn/ui (new-york) primitives are the source of truth for variants — check `/dev/ui` (DevPlayground seed) for the sanctioned Button / Input states before inventing new ones.
- **Dark mode**: verify both themes via the `.dark` class — don't tune light only.
- **Baseline APIs only**: stick to "Widely available" CSS/JS (Container Queries, `:has()`, `<dialog>`, view-transitions, `scroll-snap`). Avoid "Newly available" (e.g. `scheduler.yield()`).

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML first: prefer `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>` over `<div role="...">`.
- ARIA only where semantic HTML is insufficient.
- Loading states: `role="status"` + `aria-live="polite"`.
- Error states: `role="alert"` + `aria-live="assertive"`.
- Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements must be keyboard-reachable.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`: gate non-essential motion (`tw-animate-css` animations, transitions) behind the query — the global `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` reset lives in `src/index.css`.
- shadcn/ui components include accessibility by default — don't override without reason.

## Path Aliases

`@/` maps to `src/`. **Only use `@/` aliases — never relative `../../`.**

```typescript
import { useUserStore } from '@/store/user/userStore';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
```
